If is use in C language. It is used to check the condition. If the condition is true then it will execute the statement. If the condition is false then it will not execute the statement. It is used to check the condition. If the condition is true then it will execute the statement. If the condition is false then it will not execute the statement.


If-else statement in C is use to check the condition. If the condition is true then it will execute the statement and return true. If the condition is false then it will execute the else statement.